Package game

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ActionFactory
    The abstract class for implementing behaviors.
    Throwable
    Interface that defines object that can be throw.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Application
    The main driver class for the entire project, entry point of the game.
    DoctorMaybe
    The class that implements MiniBoss: Doctor Maybe.
    Door
    Class that implements the door functionality as an extension of map objects.
    Floor  
    FollowBehaviour
    The behavior for an actor to keep following another actor.
    GetHeal
    action that can be triggered when having a medicine item
    GiveAction
    Class for an actor to give an item to another actor.
    GiveAndDisappearAction
    Class for the give and disappear action.
    Goon
    Class for character Goons.
    Grunt
    The class for Grunts, Grunts follows and attacks the player.
    Key
    A class that defines the key item, used to unlock locked doors.
    MagicPill
    The class for magic pills, magic pills modifies an actor's damage.
    Medicine
    medicine item -- can be taken by actors directly or store in inventory and be used later
    ModifyDamage
    Action that modifies an actor's damage.
    NewActor
    Abstract Class extends from the Actor class in the engine code.
    NewPlayer
    Class representing the Player.
    Ninja
    The class for Ninjas, Ninja will throw stun powders at player if the player is within 5 distance, and backing away by 1 distance.
    Q
    Class for character Q Q will wander around the map, can talk to the player, can give/receive item from/to player, and disappears.
    RocketBody
    A class that defines the rocket body item, used to build the rocket and win the game.
    RocketEngine
    A class that defines the rocket engine item, used to build the rocket and win the game.
    RocketPad
    Class for the rocket pad location.
    RocketPlan
    A class that defines the rocket plans item, can be given to Q in exchange for the rocketBody item.
    ShoutAction
    An action for shouting an insult at other Actors.
    Soldier
    Soldier class -- soldier will always stay in the same position and trying to defend something or someone
    StunPowder
    Class for the stun powder which is an weaponItem that can be thrown by an actor and has 50% of chance to hit the target.
    SuperSoldier
    The enhanced version of Soldier, much stronger and follows the player instead of standing still.
    TalkAction
    The class for actor to Talk to each other.
    Throw
    Class for throw action
    Trap
    A trap (item), an actor has to be at its location to triggers.
    UnlockAction
    This class is the action to unlock or lock a door.
    Wall
    A regular wall (Ground object) that blocks actor from entering its location.
    WanderingBehaviour
    The class that implements wandering behavior, which makes an actor moves around the map randomly.
